{
  "stem": "812.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Adults were always saying that the transports that were leaving Westerbork for the-- there were weekly transports and-- that were leaving for the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "That was always a terrible burden for the adults to bear, and-- because they did know that life in the camps in Eastern Europe were dreadful, and didn't know at that point that they-- that they were extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But they did know that their lives would be endangered and that things were getting increasingly worse.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] As I said, for us children, life really was bearable.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "It was even comfortable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And-- and even with that, we were-- we welcomed to leave, only because we children did not know what was ahead of us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] that was about all in Westerbork that I-- I can remember.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And my mother worked hard in-- as a-- in the kitchen, always in the kitchen duty, and my father always with the shoes and always repairing shoes and ripping shoes apart.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And it was more busy work for them than anything else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "There were-- many very, very talented people came to Westerbork from various parts of Europe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And there was a man by the name of Willy Rosen, who was a cabaret artist.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And I remember reading-- I was never allowed to go to these cabarets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "But some of the adults did go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And of course, the cabaret was for-- mostly for the-- for the German Gestapo, for the SS.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when the people were to applaud, they were told, you don't applaud for Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And-- but of course, it was a very professional production.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "The-- the props were nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "But the talent was very professional.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
